               <birth>He was born in the province of <placeName ref="LOC2947Endart">ʾƎndartā</placeName>.
               </birth>
               <floruit notBefore="1300" notAfter="1380">
                  He was a monk of the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2313DabraM">Dabra Māryām</placeName>
                  in the 14th century and was a leader of the
                  <persName ref="PRS11207Ewostateans">ʾEwosṭātean</persName> movement. 
                  He was a pupil of <persName ref="PRS3932Ewostate">ʾEwosṭatewos</persName> of 
                  <placeName ref="LOC2358DabraS">Dabra Ṣārbi</placeName>. 
                  He is still venerated as a saint in <placeName ref="LOC2991Eritre">Eritrea</placeName> and 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5932Tegray">Tǝgrāy</placeName>. 
                  He is represented as one of "the great masters" of the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2313DabraM">Dabra Māryām</placeName>
                  together with  
                  <persName ref="PRS2050Aronof">ʾabbā
                     ʾAron of Galilā</persName> in the 
                  <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2375Synaxa">Sǝnkǝssār</ref> entry.
                  </floruit>
                  <death when="1380"/>
               </person>  
